<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 20 at 6:57AM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Kenedy,
eastern Jim Hogg, northeastern Hidalgo, northeastern Starr and Brooks
Counties through 730 AM CDT...
At 656 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles northeast of Agua Nueva, moving east at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Falfurrias, Agua Nueva, Encino, Rachal, Airport Road Addition, La
Gloria, La Reforma, Pleasant Park, San Isidro and La Colonia Park.
This includes US Highway 281 between mile markers 708 and 750.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
